<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><b>Short Description</b><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">This defines the interval after which an application with
inactive connections from connection pool will be closed. This setting will
affect applications using the HTTPS communication APIs.&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><b>Long Description</b><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">In OM scenario , opcmsga is an HTTP client which makes
Connections from the node to the BBC communication broker. If the connections
from an Http Client like opcmsga is inactive for more than a minute closing the
connection would improve the performance. Hence from OA version 11.02 and above
AUTO_CONNECTION_CLOSE_INTERVAL=60, for opcmsga.<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><br></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="font-size: 13pt; line-height: 107%; color: rgb(46, 116, 181);">CHROOT_PATH</span></span><span style="font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span></p><table class="MsoTableGrid" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="0" style="border-left: none;">
