 <tr>
  <td width="230" valign="top" style="width: 172.25pt; border-right-width: 1pt; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-right-color: black; border-bottom-color: black; border-image: initial; border-top: none; padding: 0in 5.4pt;">
  <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:
  normal"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;
  font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:major-latin;
  mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;mso-hansi-theme-font:major-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:
  &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">Related variables<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
  </td>
  <td width="504" valign="top" style="width: 5.25in; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-bottom-color: black; border-right-width: 1pt; border-right-color: black; padding: 0in 5.4pt;">
  <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:
  normal"><span style="mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;
  mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;
  mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#010101">&nbsp;</span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
</tbody></table><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="font-size: 13pt; line-height: 107%; color: rgb(46, 116, 181);"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3"><b>Short
Description</b><o:p></o:p></font></span></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3">LCore
components OvBbc as well as OvDeploy provide mechanisms to securely transfer
files from the management server to the managed node. These components permit
relative paths for the destination files. This variable is used to prevent the
applications who consumes OvBbc and OvDeploy apis, to&nbsp; not use relative paths while using the file
transfer mechanism. The default value is kept as false in order to retain the
backward compatibility.<o:p></o:p></font></span></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3"><b>Long
Description</b><o:p></o:p></font></span></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3">Deployment
component&nbsp; used to for software
installation tasks on a remote machine.<o:p></o:p></font></span></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3">The
functionalities provided are from copying files from one server to another to
copying entire directory structure from one system to another to executing
remote commands. <o:p></o:p></font></span></span></p><p class="MsoNormal">















</p><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3">However the
functionality accepts relative paths for the destination location. Though the
channel of file transfer is secure ,in certain environments and audits this can
be classified as opening doors for path traversal attack. Path traversal is the
outbreak out of a given directory structure through relative file paths in
the user input. It aims to access files and directories that are stored outside
the web root folder. An attacker could use a certain parameter of the file path
for instance to inject ../ sequences in order to navigate through the file system.
In order to prevent any mishaps due to this , there is this new variable
DISABLE_REL_PATH introduced under namespaces bbc.fx and depl. Enabling this
variable to true would prevent the application from accessing relative paths.<o:p></o:p></font></span></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3"><br></font></span></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_Toc491176827"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="font-size:13.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;line-height:107%;mso-ascii-font-family:
&quot;Calibri Light&quot;;mso-ascii-theme-font:major-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
mso-fareast-theme-font:major-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;;
mso-hansi-theme-font:major-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
mso-bidi-theme-font:major-bidi;color:#2E74B5;mso-themecolor:accent1;mso-themeshade:
191">DISABLE_DNS</span></span></a><span class="LabelChar"><span style="font-size:
13.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;line-height:107%;mso-ascii-font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;;
mso-ascii-theme-font:major-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
mso-fareast-theme-font:major-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;;
mso-hansi-theme-font:major-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
