<p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="font-size: 13pt; line-height: 107%; color: rgb(46, 116, 181);"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></span><b style="font-size: medium; color: windowtext; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">Short
Description</b></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3">OvCtrl
module provides the ovcd process which monitors all the registered processes.
Any process can be registered for monitoring or reporting with ovcd if the
process registers with ovcd using the documented registration process. Ovcd
process internally uses the a state pattern to manage the transition of the
registered process from start through its monitoring to its end.<o:p></o:p></font></span></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3"><b>Long
Description</b><o:p></o:p></font></span></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3">Any process
that needs to be monitored or controlled using ovcd process needs to register
itself with ovcd using the ovcreg utility. If a process is registered for both
monitoring and control by ovcd, there is this variable PROCESS_TIMEOUT that
control the process state from state Stopped to Start. Based on the
registration file the process may have an initialize state as well before the
start state. When ovcd is starting a process ,the PROCESS_TIMEOUT is the
timeout value that ovcd will waits before initialize state is complete. If
the process do not complete the initialize state before this timeout value ,
the process state is reported as aborted and ovcd cleans up the process state.
Similarly if an ovc stop is issued and the time that the process takes to
stop&nbsp; crosses the timeout , the process
is force killed by ovcd. <o:p></o:p></font></span></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3">There are
certain systems where the initialization of a process takes longer; In those
systems ovc start may fail in staring the process. In such environments kill
the process and configure an increased PROCESS_TIMEOUT and retrigger the ovc
start.<o:p></o:p></font></span></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: rgb(46, 116, 181);"><o:p style=""><font size="3">&nbsp;</font></o:p></span></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_Toc491176829"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="font-size: 13pt; line-height: 107%; color: rgb(46, 116, 181);">SSL_HANDSHAKE_TIMEOUT</span></span></a><span class="LabelChar"><span style="font-size: 13pt; line-height: 107%; color: rgb(46, 116, 181);"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p><table class="MsoTableGrid" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="0" style="border-left: none;">
